Returns a {{rlp|sentinel}} or an {{rlp|iterator}} representing the end of the {{tt|elements_view}}.

Let {{rlpi|/#Data members|base_}} be the underlying view. Equivalent to:
@1@ {{c|1=return /*sentinel*/&lt;false&gt;{ranges::end(base_)};}}.
@2@ {{c|1=return /*iterator*/&lt;false&gt;{ranges::end(base_)};}}.
@3@ {{c|1=return /*sentinel*/&lt;true&gt;{ranges::end(base_)};}}.
@4@ {{c|1=return /*iterator*/&lt;true&gt;{ranges::end(base_)};}}.

===Parameters===
(none)

===Return value===
@1,3@ {{rlp|sentinel}} which compares equal to the end iterator
@2,4@ {{rlp|iterator}} to the element following the last element

===Notes===
{{tt|end()}} returns an iterator if and only if the underlying view is a {{lconcept|common_range}}: {{c/core|elements_view&lt;V,F&gt;}} models {{lconcept|common_range}} whenever {{tt|V}} does.
